(99, 1, '2014-05-29 13:27:31', '2014-05-29 13:27:31', 'Wizard Technology founder Jeremy Summers began developing for the web over 10 years ago, and quickly launched a music streaming website. Following a move to the South West <abbr title="United Kingdom">UK</abbr> Jeremy took a full time position as Head of Technology at <a href="http://www.spicerack.co.uk" title="Spicerack" target="_blank">Spicerack Media Ltd</a>, where he worked for four years, developing bespoke online/digital solutions for National and global brands including, Estée Lauder, Philosophy, Sky, Science in Sport, Homebase, and Garnier, as well as managing the internal technology needs of Spicerack, including the building and maintenance of the company website, intranet and servers. Whilst remaining good friends with Spicerack, Jeremy recently founded <a href="http://wizard.technology">Wizard Technology</a>, allowing him to serve clients on similar traffic driving projects, as well as begi development of Wizard Technology branded products.\n\nHaving been a competitive cyclist for many years, Jeremy loves to train and compete in <a href="http://www.cyclingtimetrials.org.uk/" title="CTT" target="_blank">Cycling Time Trials</a>, which he finds to contain the perfect balance of technology, analysis, determination and fun! In fact, Wizard Technology has plans to build an analytical database for power based training in 2014. \n\nJeremy has a First-class honours degree in Applied Computing (<abbr title="Bachelor of Science">BSc</abbr>) from <a href="http://home.bournemouth.ac.uk/" title="Bournemouth University" target="_blank">Bournemouth University</a>, with an official letter of commendation. \n\n', 'About', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '11-autosave-v1', '', '', '2014-05-29 13:27:31', '2014-05-29 13:27:31', '', 11, 'http://wizard.technology/11-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
